      "repeat": false,
      "desc": "Water quality.",
      "narrative": "At the time of inspection, water quality records for the nine California sea lions showed that the pH and chlorine levels\nwere not tested on January 26th and 28th, 2026. Failure to test pH and chlorine levels daily can negatively impact the\nhealth and well-being of the animals, as well as overall water quality, resulting in possible ocular, skin, and respiratory\nirritation and bacterial proliferation. Water samples shall be taken and tested at least weekly for coliform count and at least\ndaily for pH and any chemical additives (e.g., chlorine and copper) that are added to the water to maintain water quality\nstandards.\nCorrect by: March 27, 2026\nThis inspection and exit interview were conducted with facility representatives.\nn"
    }
  ],
  "narrative": "3.106(b)(3) \n   \nWater quality. \nAt the time of inspection, water quality records for the nine California sea lions showed that the pH and chlorine levels \nwere not tested on January 26th and 28th, 2026. Failure to test pH and chlorine levels daily can negatively impact the \nhealth and well-being of the animals, as well as overall water quality, resulting in possible ocular, skin, and respiratory \nirritation and bacterial proliferation. Water samples shall be taken and tested at least weekly for coliform count and at least \ndaily for pH and any chemical additives (e.g., chlorine and copper) that are added to the water to maintain water quality \nstandards.  \n \nCorrect by: March 27, 2026 \n \nThis inspection and exit interview were conducted with facility representatives. \n \n n",
